<!DOCTYPE html>
{# VERDICT report template - checklist item 9.
   Spec ref: spec.md > Orchestrator > Report generator (report/);
             spec.md > Data Flow - Lifecycle of a Finding.
   A single self-contained file: inline CSS only, NO <script>, NO external
   <link>, anchors only. Citations are <a href="#ledger-<seq>"> that jump into
   the embedded ledger rendering (Appendix C), where each tool_result line
   carries id="ledger-<seq>". Opens offline, nothing to run. #}
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>VERDICT report - {{ case_name }}</title>
  <style>
    :root {
      --critical: #b91c1c; --high: #c2410c; --medium: #b45309; --low: #0e7490;
      --verified: #15803d; --unconfirmed: #b45309; --refuted: #b91c1c;
      --ink: #1f2933; --muted: #5b6573; --line: #d6dbe1; --bg-soft: #f6f8fa;
    }
    * { box-sizing: border-box; }
    body {
      font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto,
        Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
      color: var(--ink); line-height: 1.5; margin: 0;
      padding: 2rem 1.5rem 4rem; max-width: 60rem; margin: 0 auto;
    }
    h1 { font-size: 1.7rem; margin: 0 0 .25rem; }
    h2 {
      font-size: 1.25rem; margin: 2.25rem 0 .75rem;
      border-bottom: 2px solid var(--line); padding-bottom: .25rem;
    }
    h3 { font-size: 1.05rem; margin: 1.5rem 0 .4rem; }
    a { color: #1d4ed8; }
    p { margin: .5rem 0; }
    code, pre, .mono {
      font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
      font-size: .82rem;
    }
    pre {
      background: var(--bg-soft); border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 4px; padding: .6rem .75rem; overflow-x: auto;
      white-space: pre-wrap; word-break: break-word; margin: .4rem 0;
    }
    .muted { color: var(--muted); }
    .meta-grid {
      display: grid; grid-template-columns: max-content 1fr; gap: .25rem 1.25rem;
      margin: .75rem 0 0; font-size: .95rem;
    }
    .meta-grid dt { color: var(--muted); }
    .meta-grid dd { margin: 0; font-weight: 600; }
    table { border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; margin: .75rem 0; font-size: .92rem; }
    th, td { text-align: left; padding: .45rem .6rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); vertical-align: top; }
    th { background: var(--bg-soft); font-size: .8rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .03em; color: var(--muted); }
    .sev { font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; font-size: .78rem; letter-spacing: .03em; }
    .sev-critical { color: var(--critical); }
    .sev-high { color: var(--high); }
    .sev-medium { color: var(--medium); }
    .sev-low { color: var(--low); }
    .verdict { font-weight: 700; font-size: .8rem; }
    .verdict-VERIFIED { color: var(--verified); }
    .verdict-UNCONFIRMED { color: var(--unconfirmed); }
    .verdict-REFUTED { color: var(--refuted); }
    .finding { border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 6px; padding: .25rem 1rem 1rem; margin: 1rem 0; }
    .finding-head { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: .5rem 1rem; align-items: baseline; }
    .excerpt-path { font-size: .8rem; color: var(--muted); margin: .6rem 0 .15rem; }
    .note { background: #fef9c3; border: 1px solid #fde047; border-radius: 4px; padding: .5rem .75rem; margin: .6rem 0; font-size: .9rem; }
    .empty { color: var(--muted); font-style: italic; padding: .5rem 0; }
    .ledger-entry { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); padding: .35rem 0; }
    .ledger-entry:target { background: #fff7d6; outline: 2px solid #fde047; }
    .ledger-seq { font-weight: 700; color: var(--muted); }
    sup a { text-decoration: none; }
    footer { margin-top: 3rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--line); color: var(--muted); font-size: .82rem; }
    @media print {
      body { padding: 0; max-width: none; }
      h2 { page-break-after: avoid; }
      .finding, .ledger-entry { page-break-inside: avoid; }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

{# ----------------------------------------------------- 1. Header ------- #}
<header>
  <h1>VERDICT &mdash; Investigation Report</h1>
  <p class="muted">Autonomous, self-verified DFIR triage with a server-written audit ledger.</p>
  <dl class="meta-grid">
    <dt>Case</dt><dd>{{ case_name }}</dd>
    <dt>Run ID</dt><dd class="mono">{{ run_id }}</dd>
    <dt>Wall time</dt><dd>{{ wall_time }}</dd>
    <dt>Total API cost</dt><dd>${{ "%.4f"|format(total_cost) }}</dd>
    <dt>Model</dt><dd class="mono">{{ model }}</dd>
    <dt>Findings</dt><dd>{{ verified_unconfirmed|length }} reported &middot; {{ refuted|length }} refuted</dd>
  </dl>
  {% if interrupted %}
  <div class="note"><strong>Run INTERRUPTED.</strong> This is a partial report written from the findings that existed when the run was interrupted.</div>
  {% endif %}
  {% for note in budget_notes %}
  <div class="note"><strong>Budget guard:</strong> {{ note }}</div>
  {% endfor %}
</header>

{# --------------------------------------------- 2. Executive summary ---- #}
<section>
  <h2>1. Executive summary</h2>
  {% if executive_summary %}
  <p>{{ executive_summary }}</p>
  {% else %}
  <p class="empty">No executive summary was produced.</p>
  {% endif %}
</section>

{# --------------------------------------------- 3. Attack narrative ----- #}
<section>
  <h2>2. Attack narrative</h2>
  {% if attack_narrative %}
  <p>
    {% for s in attack_narrative %}{{ s.text }}{% if s.finding_id %}<sup><a href="#{{ s.finding_id }}">[{{ s.finding_id }}]</a></sup>{% endif %} {% endfor %}
  </p>
  {% else %}
  <p class="empty">No attack narrative &mdash; the evidence examined showed no chain of intrusion to recount.</p>
  {% endif %}
</section>

{# --------------------------------------------- 4. Findings table ------- #}
<section>
  <h2>3. Findings</h2>
  <p class="muted">Verified and unconfirmed findings only. Refuted claims are in Appendix A.</p>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>ID</th><th>Claim</th><th>Severity</th><th>Confidence</th><th>ATT&amp;CK</th><th>Evidence</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
    {% for f in verified_unconfirmed %}
      <tr>
        <td class="mono"><a href="#{{ f.id }}">{{ f.id }}</a></td>
        <td>{{ f.claim }}</td>
        <td class="sev sev-{{ f.severity }}">{{ f.severity }}</td>
        <td class="verdict verdict-{{ f.verdict }}">{{ f.verdict }}</td>
        <td class="mono">{{ f.attack_id }}</td>
        <td>{{ f.cites|length }}</td>
      </tr>
    {% endfor %}
    {% if not verified_unconfirmed %}
      <tr><td colspan="6" class="empty">No findings &mdash; the evidence was examined and found clean. No indicators of compromise were reported.</td></tr>
    {% endif %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
</section>

{# --------------------------------------------- 5. Per-finding detail --- #}
<section>
  <h2>4. Finding detail</h2>
  {% if not verified_unconfirmed %}
  <p class="empty">No reported findings to detail.</p>
  {% endif %}
  {% for f in verified_unconfirmed %}
  <div class="finding" id="{{ f.id }}">
    <div class="finding-head">
      <h3 style="margin:.6rem 0 0">{{ f.id }}</h3>
      <span class="sev sev-{{ f.severity }}">{{ f.severity }}</span>
      <span class="verdict verdict-{{ f.verdict }}">{{ f.verdict }}</span>
      <span class="mono muted">{{ f.attack_id }}</span>
    </div>
    <p>{{ f.claim }}</p>
    <h4 style="margin:.6rem 0 .2rem; font-size:.92rem;">Evidence</h4>
    {% if f.evidence %}
      {% for e in f.evidence %}
      <div>
        <div class="excerpt-path">
          cite <a href="#ledger-{{ e.cite_seq }}">seq {{ e.cite_seq }}</a>
          &middot; <span class="mono">{{ e.tool }}</span>
          {% if e.output_path %}&middot; <span class="mono">{{ e.output_path }}</span>{% endif %}
        </div>
        {% if e.excerpt %}<pre>{{ e.excerpt }}</pre>{% else %}<p class="empty">(no excerpt available for this artifact)</p>{% endif %}
      </div>
      {% endfor %}
    {% else %}
      <p class="empty">No reproducible artifacts were resolved for this finding's citations.</p>
    {% endif %}
    <h4 style="margin:.8rem 0 .2rem; font-size:.92rem;">Verifier's reproduction note</h4>
    <p>{% if f.verdict_reason %}{{ f.verdict_reason }}{% else %}<span class="empty">(no verdict reason recorded)</span>{% endif %}</p>
  </div>
  {% endfor %}
</section>

{# --------------------------------------- 6. Appendix A: refuted -------- #}
<section>
  <h2>Appendix A &mdash; Refuted findings</h2>
  <p class="muted">Triage hypotheses the adversarial verifier reproduced and broke. Their presence here is proof the self-correction fired &mdash; they were kept out of the headline findings above.</p>
  {% if refuted %}
    {% for f in refuted %}
    <div class="finding" id="{{ f.id }}">
      <div class="finding-head">
        <h3 style="margin:.6rem 0 0">{{ f.id }}</h3>
        <span class="sev sev-{{ f.severity }}">{{ f.severity }}</span>
        <span class="verdict verdict-REFUTED">REFUTED</span>
        <span class="mono muted">{{ f.attack_id }}</span>
      </div>
      <p><strong>Claim (refuted):</strong> {{ f.claim }}</p>
      <p><strong>Refutation:</strong> {% if f.verdict_reason %}{{ f.verdict_reason }}{% else %}<span class="empty">(no refutation reason recorded)</span>{% endif %}</p>
      {% if f.cites %}<p class="muted">Cited evidence:
        {% for seq in f.cites %}<a href="#ledger-{{ seq }}">seq {{ seq }}</a>{% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}{% endfor %}
      </p>{% endif %}
    </div>
    {% endfor %}
  {% else %}
    <p class="empty">No findings were refuted in this run.</p>
  {% endif %}
</section>

{# ------------------------------ 7. Appendix B: evidence inventory ------ #}
<section>
  <h2>Appendix B &mdash; Evidence inventory</h2>
  {% if inventory %}
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>File</th><th>Type</th><th>Size (bytes)</th><th>SHA-256</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
    {% for item in inventory %}
      <tr>
        <td class="mono">{{ item.path }}</td>
        <td>{{ item.type }}</td>
        <td>{{ item.size if item.size is not none else "?" }}</td>
        <td class="mono" style="word-break:break-all">{{ item.sha256 }}</td>
      </tr>
    {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
  {% else %}
  <p class="empty">No evidence inventory was recorded for this run.</p>
  {% endif %}
</section>

{# ------------------------ 8. Appendix C: tool-call index / ledger ------ #}
<section>
  <h2>Appendix C &mdash; Tool-call index (audit ledger)</h2>
  <p class="muted">Every ledger event, in order. Each tool result is anchored
    <span class="mono">ledger-&lt;seq&gt;</span> &mdash; the citations above jump here.
    The ledger is written by the server only (single writer); this is a faithful rendering of <span class="mono">ledger.jsonl</span>.</p>
  {% for entry in ledger %}
  <div class="ledger-entry"{% if entry.event == "tool_result" %} id="ledger-{{ entry.seq }}"{% endif %}>
    <span class="ledger-seq">#{{ entry.seq }}</span>
    <span class="mono">{{ entry.ts }}</span>
    <strong>{{ entry.event }}</strong>
    {% if entry.tool %}<span class="mono">{{ entry.tool }}</span>{% endif %}
    {% if entry.summary %}<span class="muted">{{ entry.summary }}</span>{% endif %}
  </div>
  {% endfor %}
  {% if not ledger %}<p class="empty">No ledger events were recorded.</p>{% endif %}
</section>

{# ------------------------ 9. Appendix D: methodology ------------------- #}
<section>
  <h2>Appendix D &mdash; Methodology &amp; constraints</h2>
  <p>This investigation was produced by VERDICT, an autonomous agent whose safety is
    enforced by architecture, not by prompts. The agent's only actuators are a fixed
    set of typed, read-only forensic tools placed in its tool list for the current
    phase. Specifically, by construction:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>No shell, no file-write tool.</strong> There is no tool that accepts an arbitrary
      command string and no tool that writes to evidence &mdash; the harmful capability does not
      exist in the agent's tool list, so it cannot be enabled by a prompt.</li>
    <li><strong>Typed, validated parameters.</strong> Every tool call is validated server-side;
      malformed calls are rejected and recorded in the ledger.</li>
    <li><strong>Server-side path guard.</strong> Tools may read only from the evidence folder and
      write only to this run's output folder; any path outside either is refused by the server.</li>
    <li><strong>Single-writer ledger.</strong> The audit ledger is written exclusively by the
      server, one fsync'd line per event; the agent has no tool that can write or modify it.</li>
    <li><strong>Independent verification.</strong> Every reported finding was re-derived by a
      separate adversarial pass in a fresh context with a restricted toolset, working only from
      the raw evidence the finding cited. Refuted claims (Appendix A) are kept out of the headline.</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="muted">Pcap files, if present, are inventoried and hashed but not parsed (deep packet
    analysis is out of scope for this run).</p>
</section>

<footer>
  Generated by VERDICT &mdash; run <span class="mono">{{ run_id }}</span> &middot;
  model <span class="mono">{{ model }}</span> &middot; total cost ${{ "%.4f"|format(total_cost) }}.
  Self-contained HTML: open offline, no server required.
</footer>

</body>
</html>
